The White House announced that President Obama will hold two events to highlight the administration's commitment to saving families money at the pump, reducing oil consumption, and creating jobs. On August 9th, the President will announce first-of-their-kind fuel-efficiency standards for work trucks, buses, and heavy-duty vehicles. On August 11th, he will tour an advanced battery facility in Michigan to highlight the role of innovative technologies in achieving fuel-economy standards. The White House also provided updates on the FAA dispute, the stock market, and the President's 50th birthday celebrations. The press briefing also covered topics such as the economy, defense cuts, the Middle East peace process, and foreign aid to China.